  <section id=3D"pitch">
    <h2 id=3D"pitch-h">The 30-second pitch <span class=3D"tag">say this if =
they open with "walk me through it"</span></h2>
    <div class=3D"callout pitch">
      <p>"It's a task manager built on top of a bare-bones starter =E2=80=
=94 the starter only had a DB connection and one GET route with a placehold=
er UI. I built out full CRUD (create, toggle done/todo, delete), sorting on=
 every column, and status/priority filtering. On the backend I layered it p=
roperly =E2=80=94 routes =E2=86=92 controllers =E2=86=92 validators =E2=86=
=92 models =E2=86=92 db =E2=80=94 added centralized error handling, request=
 logging, and two-tier rate limiting. On the frontend, the whole task list =
is fetched once and cached in a reducer; filtering and sorting are pure cli=
ent-side view transforms over that cache, so they're instant with zero extr=
a network calls. Every mutation patches the cache from its own response ins=
tead of re-fetching the list."</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id=3D"architecture">
    <h2>Architecture</h2>
    <div class=3D"flow">
      <span class=3D"node">React UI</span><span class=3D"arrow">=E2=86=92</=
span>
      <span class=3D"node">fetch() in api/tasks.ts</span><span class=3D"arr=
ow">=E2=86=92</span>
      <span class=3D"node">Vite dev proxy /api</span><span class=3D"arrow">=
